==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Embower
<hw>Em*bow"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To cover with a
bower; to shelter with trees.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>imbower</asp>.]</altsp> <mark>[Poetic]</mark> <au>Milton.</au> --
<def2><pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To lodge or rest in a bower.</def>
<mark>[Poetic]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧In their wide boughs <xex>embow'ring.</xex>
⟦rdquo⟧</def2> <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Embowl</ent>⟦br⟧
